subject:

THE FUTILITY OF PRIDE
===================================================================
verse:
"Blessed are the poor in spirit, for their's is the
kingdom of heaven." (Mt. 5:3)

===================================================================
reflection:

What we should recognize in this verse is that we must be
willing to assume the role of a beggar to enter into the
kingdom of heaven. Why? because pride will cause us not to
admit we are wrong or have compassion on our fellow man. It
can even cause us to live beyond our means (Ro. 13:8). Pride
also leads to rebellion (Ps. 10:4) and it can even cause us
to drift from our religious belief (I Tim. 3:6). There is a
Chinese proverb which goes something like this: "He who
stands on a pedestal has no place to go but to step down.
("pedestal" meaning pride)

===================================================================
prayer:

Humble King, teach me the poverty of spirit that opens the
door to Your kingdom. Break the grip of pride in me—grant
repentance, compassion, and contentment—so I may step down
from every pedestal and walk low with You. Fill me with Your
grace to depend on You alone. Amen. (AI)
